    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-06T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="421"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 322.112J72/1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                        General <persName type="to">Goding</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-06T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 5, 8 a.m. Legation has been instructed to report on imprisonment of
                    Jones. Department will keep you advised and desires that for the present you
                    continue to report directly to it as well as to the Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
